<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="whose-pron">whose <strong><em>pron</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /huːz/    美 /huːz/  </p>
<p>[who 或 which 的所有格]</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>[疑问代词] 谁的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Whose dictionary is it?
这是谁的字典?</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>[连接代词，引导名词性从句] 谁的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Whose car was stolen must be made clear.
必须查清楚是谁的车被偷了。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I wonder whose these keys are. 
我想知道这些钥匙是谁的。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The first thing we should discuss is whose home is the nearest to school. 
我们应该讨论的第一件事是，谁家离学校最近。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>[关系代词，引导定语从句] 那个 / 些人的；他 /她 / 它的；他们 / 她们 / 它们的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Rescue workers built shelters for survivors whose homes had been destroyed.
救援人员为那些家园被毁的幸存者盖起了避难所。</p><footer>人教① – 4改</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The school shop, whose customers are mainly students, is closed for the holidays.
这个学校商店的顾客主要是学生，它在假期时不营业。</p><footer>2011 四川</footer></div>

<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>Dr. Roman, <strong><em>_</em></strong> secretary resigned two weeks ago, has had to do all his typing.  （2020 天津改）  </li>
<li>In ancient China lived an artist <strong><em>_</em></strong> paintings were almost lifelike.  （2020 全国）  </li>
<li>In 1963 the UN set up the World Food Programme, one of <strong><em>_</em></strong> purposes is to relieve worldwide starvation.  （2017 江苏改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. whose  2. whose  3. whose  </p></div>